class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hx</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ne_zero_iff</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mpr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Units</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ne_zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hx</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩⟩</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>in a PR and then delegated, but it occurs to me that actually I'm still not at all perfect on indentation style. Is this OK? I <code>#print</code>ed the proof to see if that gave me any clues but it's full of <code>mp :=</code> and <code>match</code>.</p>",
